--------------------------------------------------------------------
1. DEFINITIONS
--------------------------------------------------------------------

1.1  "Software" means the source code, configuration, schemas, prompts,
     architectural patterns, and any other content contained in this
     repository, in any form, in any version.

1.2  "Derivative Work" means any product, service, fork, port,
     re-implementation, or system that (a) incorporates any portion
     of the Software, or (b) is substantially built on or copies the
     distinctive architecture of the Software, including but not
     limited to the Agentic Orbital Operating System concept, the
     Living-Orb Graphics Engine, the Council of Thirteen governance
     pattern, the AICYCLE single-voice multi-engine routing, the
     Krypteia security pattern, the orb-anchored 3D event-binding,
     or the orb-to-event glowing beam interaction.

1.3  "Ecosystem Use" means any commercial activity, in any role,
     conducted through the canonical AstranoV deployment at
     https://astranov.eu or any deployment operated under licence
     from Owner, including but not limited to acting as a vendor,
     merchant, advertiser, driver/courier, agent operator,
     content publisher, or paid service provider. A person who uses
     AstranoV solely as a consumer (to buy, browse, chat, navigate,
     or talk to Astranov, without earning revenue) is NOT engaged in
     Ecosystem Use and owes nothing.

1.4  "Turnover" means all gross revenue, in any currency, from any
     source, generated by either (i) a Derivative Work or its
     operation, or (ii) Ecosystem Use, including subscription fees,
     transaction fees, advertising revenue, in-app purchases,
     marketplace cuts, licensing fees, vendor sales, delivery fees,
     courier payouts, agent operation fees, and donations tied to
     use of the Derivative Work or to Ecosystem Use. Turnover is
     measured before any deduction for costs, taxes, refunds, or
     payment-processor fees, except that genuine refunds actually
     paid to end users may be deducted in the period they are paid.

1.5  "Quarter" means a calendar quarter (Jan-Mar, Apr-Jun, Jul-Sep,
     Oct-Dec).

