2. LICENSE GRANT
--------------------------------------------------------------------

Subject to Licensee's compliance with every other section of this
License, Owner grants Licensee a worldwide, non-exclusive, non-
transferable, revocable right to:

  (a) read, study, and run the Software for any purpose;
  (b) modify the Software and create Derivative Works;
  (c) distribute the Software and Derivative Works; and
  (d) operate Derivative Works as commercial products and hosted
      services,

PROVIDED that the royalty in Section 3 is paid, the obligations in
Sections 4 through 8 are met, and any sublicense to a third party is
made under terms no less protective than this License.

--------------------------------------------------------------------
3. ROYALTY — 3% OF TURNOVER (BUILD ON IT *OR* EARN ON IT)
--------------------------------------------------------------------

The same three-percent (3%) rate applies to BOTH paths into the
AstranoV ecosystem:

  (a) DERIVATIVE-WORK ROYALTY — if you fork, embed, or build a
      product on the Software, you pay 3% of Turnover from that
      Derivative Work.

  (b) ECOSYSTEM-USE FEE — if you earn revenue THROUGH the canonical
      AstranoV deployment (or any licensed deployment) — as a
      vendor, merchant, advertiser, courier, content publisher,
      agent operator, or any other paid role — you pay 3% of the
      Turnover so generated.

3.1  The royalty under both 3(a) and 3(b) is calculated and paid per
     Quarter on Quarter Turnover, and is owed regardless of whether
     the activity is profitable.

3.2  Where Owner operates a billing rail inside the canonical
     deployment (for example, automatically withholding the 3% from
     a payout to a vendor or courier), payment via that rail
     discharges the obligation for the Turnover routed through it.
     Off-platform Turnover (such as a vendor accepting cash) is paid
     under Section 3.3.

3.3  Off-rail payment is due within thirty (30) days of the end of
     each Quarter, in EUR or USD, by bank transfer to an account
     designated in writing by Owner.

3.4  Late payments accrue simple interest at the European Central
     Bank main refinancing rate plus four percent (4%) per annum.

--------------------------------------------------------------------
4. STARTING THRESHOLD — €300
--------------------------------------------------------------------

4.1  No royalty is owed until Licensee's total Turnover (combining
     all Derivative Works AND all Ecosystem Use under Section 3) in
     a trailing twelve-month period exceeds three hundred Euro
     (EUR 300). Below that line, use is free of fee.

4.2  Once Licensee's trailing-twelve-month Turnover crosses EUR 300,
     the 3% royalty under Section 3 applies to ALL Turnover from
     that moment forward, on a per-Quarter basis, until the trailing
     twelve-month figure falls back below the threshold.

4.3  Reporting under Section 5 is required from the first Quarter in
     which any Turnover is generated, even below the threshold, so
     the threshold crossing can be verified.

This low starting threshold exists for one reason: AstranoV is meant
to be used. A student, a side-project, a small vendor, a courier
making pocket money — everyone is welcome at zero cost. The 3% is
owed only once real commercial activity (more than EUR 300 in a
year) is underway.

--------------------------------------------------------------------
5. REPORTING & AUDIT
--------------------------------------------------------------------

5.1  With each Quarter's payment (or with each Quarter's notice that
     the exemption in Section 4 applies), Licensee shall deliver to
     Owner a written statement showing, per Derivative Work:
       (a) Turnover for the Quarter;
       (b) Trailing-twelve-month Turnover;
       (c) Royalty calculated and paid;
       (d) The product name, URL, and a one-line description of the
           Derivative Work.

5.2  Licensee shall keep complete books and records sufficient to
     verify Turnover for at least five (5) years.

5.3  Owner, or an independent auditor designated by Owner, may, on
     thirty (30) days' written notice and no more than once per
     calendar year, audit Licensee's records to verify Turnover and
     royalty. The audit is at Owner's expense unless it reveals an
     underpayment of more than five percent (5%) for the period
     audited, in which case Licensee shall bear the reasonable cost
     of the audit and pay the shortfall with interest under 3.4.

--------------------------------------------------------------------
6. ATTRIBUTION
--------------------------------------------------------------------

Every Derivative Work, in every place where it credits any third-
party software, shall include the following attribution, prominent
and legible to end users:

  "Built on AstranoV — the Agentic Orbital Operating System
   invented by Notis Astranov. https://astranov.eu"

The attribution may be condensed in space-constrained UIs (e.g. an
"About" screen, a footer, a splash screen) so long as it remains
legible and includes the name "AstranoV" and a link to
https://astranov.eu.

